# EasyCPP - C++ Made Easy 🚀

.PP
![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)

.PP
![Standard: C++17](https://img.shields.io/badge/C%2B%2B-17-blue.svg)

.PP
![Status: Active](https://img.shields.io/badge/status-active-brightgreen.svg)

.PP
**124 Python-like utility functions for modern C++\&.** 
.br

.PP
Stop writing the same boilerplate over and over\&. \fReasycpp\&.h\fP is a **single-header library** that brings the simplicity of Python to C++ without sacrificing performance\&.

.PP
## ✨ Why EasyCPP?

.PP
- **Single Header:** Just drop \fReasycpp\&.h\fP into your project and \fR#include\fP it\&.

.PP
- **No Dependencies:** Uses only the C++ Standard Library\&.

.PP
- **Zero Overhead:** \fRconstexpr\fP, \fRnoexcept\fP, and \fR\\[\\[nodiscard]]\fP everywhere\&.

.PP
- **Readable Code:** Write \fR\fBprint()\fP\fP, \fR\fBinput()\fP\fP, \fR\fBsplit()\fP\fP, \fR\fBtrim()\fP\fP instead of \fRstd::cout << \&.\&.\&. << std::endl;\fP\&.

.PP
## 🚀 Quick Example

.PP
```cpp

.PP
#include "easycpp\&.h"

.PP
using namespace std;

.PP
int main() {

.PP
&#x20; // Clean printing

.PP
&#x20; println("Hello, ", "World!"); // Supports multiple args

.PP
&#x20; // Simple input

.PP
&#x20; string name = input_str("What's your name? ");

.PP
&#x20; int age = input_int("How old are you? ");

.PP
&#x20; // String utilities

.PP
&#x20; string s = "  Hello World  ";

.PP
&#x20; println(trim(s)); // "Hello World"

.PP
&#x20; vector<string> words = split(s); // {"Hello", "World"}

.PP
&#x20; // Vector utilities

.PP
&#x20; vector<int> nums = {1, 2, 3, 4, 5};

.PP
&#x20; println("Sum: ", sum(nums)); // 15

.PP
&#x20; println("Avg: ", average(nums)); // 3\&.0

.PP
&#x20; // Colored console output

.PP
&#x20; \fBcolor_red()\fP;

.PP
&#x20; println("This is red!");

.PP
&#x20; \fBcolor_reset()\fP;

.PP
&#x20; return 0;

.PP
} 
